---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Stroke"
	heroSubtitle="Recovering from a stroke can feel overwhelming — but the right support can make a real difference. We help you regain movement, confidence and independence."
	breadcrumb="Stroke"
	seoTitle="Stroke Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Specialist stroke rehab physiotherapy in Clapham, London. Regain movement, balance and independence with tailored neurological rehabilitation."
	introImage="/condition/stroke/senior-woman-track.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/stroke/cycling-gloves.jpg"
	intro={[
		"Recovering from a stroke can feel overwhelming — but the right support can make a real difference. We focus on helping you regain movement, rebuild confidence, and improve independence, working at a pace that's right for you.",
		"Whether you're newly discharged or continuing recovery months or years on, we'll build a plan around your goals and the things you want to get back to.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get"
	symptomsHighlight="support"
	symptomsIntro="You may benefit from physiotherapy if you're experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"Weakness on one side of the body",
		"Shoulder pain and weakness on the affected side",
		"Difficulty walking or changes in your gait",
		"Problems with balance or confidence when moving",
		"Muscle stiffness or tightness",
		"Reduced coordination or control",
		"Difficulty with everyday tasks like standing, reaching, or dressing",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we"
	treatmentHighlight="help"
	treatmentIntro="Your personalised plan may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve strength, mobility, and coordination",
		"Gait and balance training to support walking and confidence",
		"Pain control",
		"Exercises to improve control and reduce stiffness",
		"Task-based rehab focused on everyday activities",
		"Support with building independence safely",
		"Access to equipment such as the AlterG treadmill where appropriate",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Those recently discharged from hospital",
		"People continuing recovery months or years post-stroke",
		"Patients seeking improved walking or mobility",
		"Those working on shoulder, arm, and hand function",
		"Anyone wanting to regain daily independence",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "When should I start physiotherapy after a stroke?", a: "As early as possible is ideal, but improvements can still be made months or years later." },
		{ q: "Can physio help me walk better?", a: "Yes — we work on strength, balance, and coordination to improve walking." },
		{ q: "What is the AlterG treadmill?", a: "It allows you to walk with reduced body weight, making movement safer and easier." },
		{ q: "Can you help with stiffness or tight muscles?", a: "Yes — we use a combination of exercises and hands-on treatment to improve movement." },
		{ q: "How often should I come?", a: "This depends on your goals, but regular sessions can help build progress more quickly." },
	]}
/>
